INSERT INTO `stock` VALUES (1,'Apple Inc.','AAPL','Apple Inc. is a technology company that engages in the design, manufacturing, and marketing of smartphones, personal computers, tablets, wearables, and related accessories and services. The company was founded in 1977. With its headquarters in Cupertino, California, Apple operates and distributes its products worldwide.','apple.png',1),(3,'Meta','META','Meta Platforms Inc is the umbrella company for all apps and technologies previously under the Facebook, Inc brand. During the 2021 rebrand, founder and CEO Mark Zuckerberg explained that the technology conglomerate was refocusing on the next chapter of the internet, which he dubs the ‘metaverse’. The metaverse will be an immersive, virtual environment that uses holographic, augmented reality and virtual reality technologies to provide a 3D digital space for gaming, communication and social interaction.','meta.png',2),(4,'Microsoft','MSFT','Microsoft Corporation is a leading American multinational technology company primarily engaged in the production of computer software, consumer electronics, personal computers, and related services. The firm was founded 1975 by Bill Gates and Paul Allen, and has its corporate headquarters in Redmond, Washington, with international offices around the world. The company operates through the following business segments: Productivity and Business Processes; Intelligent Cloud; and More Personal Computing. ','microsoft.png',2),(5,'Google','GOOG','Alphabet is a multinational conglomerate that was created in 2015 following a restructuring of the internet technology company Google, which was founded in 1998. Alphabet operates as the parent company of Google and its subsidiaries. Its aim is to make information and knowledge available for everyone. The company is headquartered in Mountain View, California, and operates around the world.','google.png',2),(6,'Nike','NKE','NIKE Inc. is an American multinational corporation that is engaged in the design, development, manufacturing, marketing and sales of footwear, apparel, sports equipment, accessories, and services for a wide variety of sports and fitness activities. It is one of the world\'s largest and best-known suppliers of athletic shoes, apparel, and accessories. The company is headquartered near Beaverton, Oregon, in the Portland metropolitan area. The firm was originally founded in 1964 as Blue Ribbon Sports and became Nike Inc. in 1971.','nike.png',3),(7,'Netflix','NFLX','Netflix, Inc. is an American online entertainment and TV production company that offers a subscription streaming service to clients within the USA and internationally. Launched in 1997, the firm offers a library of films, documentaries, and television series through distribution deals with other networks and production companies, as well as its own productions, known as Netflix Originals. The firm has its corporate headquarters in Los Gatos, California.','netflix.png',2),(8,'Adobe','ADBE','Adobe Systems, Inc. is a software company that develops and publishes marketing and media solutions for individual and business customers. Charles M. Geschke and John E. Warnock founded the company in 1982. Adobe Systems is based in San Jose, California, and distributes its software products worldwide. The company has office locations in North America, Asia, Australia, New Zealand, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and South America.','adobe.png',2),(9,'Zoom Inc.','ZM','Zoom Video Communications, Inc. provides a video-first communications platform to customers worldwide. The company offers Zoom Meetings, which support HD video, voice, chat, and content sharing through a wide range of devices. Founded in 2011, Zoom has its headquarters in San Jose, California.','zoom.png',2),(11,'Nvidia','NVDA','NVIDIA Corporation is an American multinational technology company based in Santa Clara, California. The company is engaged in the design, manufacture and marketing of graphics processing units (GPUs) for the gaming and professional markets, as well as system on a chip units (SoCs) for the automotive and mobile computing industries. The firm was founded in 1993. ','nvidia.png',1),(12,'HubSpot','HUBS','HubSpot Inc. is an American company engaged in the design, development and marketing of software products for inbound marketing, sales, and customer service. The firm was founded in 2005 by two MIT graduates, fascinated by the concept of inbound marketing. The firm is headquartered in Cambridge, Massachusetts, and serves an international customer base, working with businesses in a variety of verticals, primarily located in the United States, Canada, Latin America, Europe, and Asia Pacific.','hubspot.png',2),(13,'Laboratory Corp','LH','Laboratory Corp. of America Holdings, or LabCorp, is a life sciences and diagnostics company. LabCorp’s services include lead optimisation, analytical services, and clinical trials. Founded in 1969 and headquartered in Burlington, North Carolina, the company operates internationally. LabCorp trades on the NYSE using the ticker LH. Diversify your investment portfolio when you buy LH stock.','lab.png',4),(14,'Energy Transfer','ET','Energy Transfer LP is an energy company operating within the United States. The company owns and manages a diversified portfolio of energy assets with a strategic footprint in all of the major domestic production basins. Founded in 1996, Energy Transfer has its headquarters in Dallas, Texas.','energyt.png',5),(15,'KBR Inc','KBR','Founded in 1998, KBR, Inc. provides scientific, technology, and engineering solutions to governments and commercial sectors. These services include life-cycle support solutions, systems engineering, and logistics. With its headquarters in Houston, Texas, the company operates worldwide and is listed on the NYSE under the ticker KBR. Learn more about the KBR share price by adding this item to your eToro watchlist.','kbr.png',2),(16,'Walmart Inc.','WMT','Walmart Inc. is a leading retailer that operates wholesale stores, e-commerce stores, and other units and outlets. Founded in 1962, the company was first known as Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. and changed its name to Walmart, Inc. in February 2018. With its headquarters in Bentonville, Arkansas, it operates in the United States and internationally. As of December 2021, Walmart operates approximately 10,500 stores and clubs under 48 banners in 24 different countries and e-commerce sites.','walmart.png',3),(17,'Stryker Corp','SYK','Stryker Corp. offers medical technology products, such as surgical, orthopaedic, spine, and neurotechnology products. Operating internationally, the company was founded in 1941 and is based in Kalamazoo, Michigan. Stryker is listed on the NYSE under the ticker SYK. Learn about the latest SYK stock news by adding this instrument to your eToro watchlist.','stryker.png',1),(18,'Deere & Co','DE','Deere & Co is an international American company that operates across three business segments: agriculture and turf, construction and forestry, and financial services. Headquartered in Moline, Illinois, Deere & Co was incorporated in 1868 and is listed on the NYSE with the ticker DE. Follow this instrument on eToro to monitor DE value changes.','deere.png',6),(19,'Apellis','APLS','Apellis Pharmaceuticals, Inc. is a commercial-stage biopharmaceutical company that is focused on developing therapeutic compounds to treat disease through the inhibition of the complement system. The Company is developing pegcetacoplan with Sobi for systemic administration in several indications, including paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria, C3 glomerulopathy, immune complex membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis, amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, cold agglutinin disease, and hematopoietic stem cell transplantation thrombotic microangiopathy. ','apellis.png',4),(20,'Home Depot Inc.','HD','The Home Depot, Inc. is an American home improvement retailer supplying tools, hardware, construction products, and services through a network of retail outlets in the US, Canada, and Mexico. Headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia, and founded in 1978, the firm trades on the NYSE under the ticker HD. Learn more about this instrument when you track HD stock on eToro.','homedepot.png',3),(21,'Jabil Inc.','JBL','Jabil Inc. is a manufacturing services company that offers electronic circuit designs, firmware development, and rapid prototyping solutions. Founded in 1966, the company has its headquarters in Saint Petersburg, Florida, and operates internationally in more than 30 countries. Jabil uses the ticker JBL on the NYSE. Manage news and updates on JBL share price trends with your eToro watchlist.','jabil.png',1),(22,'Pure Storage','PSTG','Pure Storage is a computer hardware company listed on the NYSE with the ticker PSTG. Founded in 2009 and based in Mountain View, California, the firm offers cloud storage and data protection services to customers worldwide. Add this instrument to your watchlist to stay up to date on the PSTG price chart.','purestorage.png',1),(23,'Palo Alto','PANW','Palo Alto Networks Inc. is an American multinational technology corporation and the world\'s leading cybersecurity company. Founded in 2005, the firm operates as a global online security platform, offering cyberattack prevention solutions to more than 85,000 customers, including a number of Fortune 100 companies, across more than 150 countries worldwide. Palo Alto Networks Inc. generated over $4 billion in revenue in the fiscal year of 2021. The firm is headquartered in Santa Clara, California.','paloalto.png',2),(24,'Block Inc.','SQ','Square Inc. changed its corporate name to Block Inc. in December of 2021. The Square name will continue to apply to the company’s seller business, which provides an integrated ecosystem of commerce solutions, business software, and banking services for sellers. While Block Inc. will be the name for the company as a corporate entity, the seller business will now own the Square brand. The company, founded in 2009, is headquartered in San Francisco.','block.png',2),(25,'PPL Corp','PPL','PPL Corporation, in conjunction with its subsidiaries, is an electricity and natural gas utility provider. Operating in the United States and United Kingdom, the company has its headquarters in Allentown, Pennsylvania. PPL Corporation was founded in 1920 and is listed on the NYSE under the ticker PPL. Diversify your eToro investment portfolio by buying PPL stock.','ppl.png',7),(26,'Arch Capital','ACGL','Arch Capital Group Ltd is an international insurance company based in Bermuda. Founded in 2001, the firm is engaged in the provision of insurance, reinsurance, and mortgage insurance to a worldwide customer base. The company is listed on the NASDAQ GS where it trades under the ticker ACGL. Get instant updates when you follow the ACGL price chart on eToro.','arch.png',8),(27,'Datadog Inc.','DDOG','Established in 2010, Datadog Inc. is a technology company with its headquarters in New York City. The company offers a range of cloud-based software solutions, providing a monitoring and analytics platform for business users, developers and IT professionals. Early investors in the firm included Index Ventures, OpenView Venture Partners and ICONIQ Strategic Partners.','datadog.png',2),(28,'Alphabet Inc.','GOOGL','Alphabet Inc. is a multinational conglomerate which originally derived from the internet tech giant Google, founded in 1998. When Google underwent a restructuring process in October 2015, it created Alphabet as its parent or holding company. The purpose of the company remains very much the same since it was established, to make information and knowledge available for everyone. This is primarily through the Google Search function and other apps, such as Maps, YouTube and Google Play. Alphabet is headquartered in Mountain View, California and operates around the globe.','alphabet.png',2),(29,'Allianz SE','ALV.DE','Allianz SE is an integrated financial services provider with global operations that provides property and casualty insurance, asset management, and life and health insurance. Founded in 1890, the company has its headquarters in Munich, Germany. Listed on the XETRA stock exchange, Allianz uses the ALV.DE ticker. Access the most recent ALV.DE stock news by adding this instrument to your eToro watchlist.','allianz.png',8),(30,'Papa John\'s','PZZA','Papa John\'s International Inc is an American pizza restaurant franchise with its headquarters in Louisville, Kentucky. It operates more than 500 company-owned restaurant locations, along with around 4,800 franchised restaurants in 45 countries around the world, employing around 16,500 people. The firm predominantly offers take-out and delivery options and is one of the largest pizza delivery restaurant chains in the United States. The firm was established in 1983.','papa.png',9),(31,'Stem Inc.','STEM','Stem, Inc. is an American energy company engaged in AI-enabled smart energy storage, delivering and operating battery storage solutions that maximize renewable energy generation and enable greener, cleaner energy solutions. The company operates across 950 sites, working with more than 40 utility partners, in 75 locations across 260 cities, primarily within the United States. The firm was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in San Francisco, California.','stem.png',6),(32,'General Electric','GE','General Electric Company (GE) is American multinational globally diversified technology and financial services company. The company\'s products and services have impacted nine different major US industries, perhaps most notably transportation, power, and healthcare. The firm’s products include aircraft engines, power generation, water processing, household appliances, medical imaging equipment, business and consumer financing, and industrial products. The company can trace its history back to 1892 and is headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts.','generalelec.png',8),(33,'General Motors','GM','General Motors Company is an American multinational corporation primarily engaged in the design, manufacture, and distribution of vehicles and vehicle parts. The firm was founded in 1908 and has its headquarters in Detroit, Michigan. General Motors is listed on the NYSE under the ticker GM. Learn more about GM stock when you track this instrument on eToro.','generalmot.png',10),(34,'SiTime Corp.','SITM','SiTime Corp is a semiconductor company that operates internationally. The majority of the company\'s business is conducted in Taiwan, Hong Kong, and the US. Products produced by the company include clock integrated circuits, resonators, MHz and kHz rated oscillators, programmable OCXOs, ruggedized oscillators, and embedded resonators. Having begun operations in 2005, the company has headquarters in Santa Clara, California. ','sitime.png',1),(35,'Box Inc.','BOX','Box, Inc. offers a cloud content management platform that supports the secure management of cloud content. Operating internationally, the company\'s platform allows users to collaborate with both internal and external parties on any device. Founded in 2005, Box, Inc. has its headquarters in Redwood City, California.','box.png',2),(36,'Seagen Inc.','SGEN','Seattle Genetics Inc. was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Bothell, Washington. The multi-product, global biotechnology company focuses on developing antibody-drug conjugate technology delivering cancer-killing therapy to tumor cells, meant for lymphoma patients. Seattle Genetics has collaborations with a line of biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies, including Bayer Pharma, Celldex Therapeutics, Genentech, Pfizer, and others, and maintains a co-development agreement with Agensys Inc. Interested in trading Seattle Genetics stocks? Follow this instrument for news and updates.','seagen.png',1),(37,'Corteva Inc.','CTVA','Corteva, Inc. is engaged in the provision of agricultural products. The company is headquartered in Wilmington, Delaware, USA and serves clients in various regions throughout the world, including the United States, Canada, Latin America, the Asia Pacific region, Europe, the Middle East, and Africa. Corteva was borne out of a company originally established in 1897 — when founder H. H. Dow developed his first agricultural product in the USA — although the brand Corteva AgriscienceTM was not developed until 2018. Originally established as part of DowDuPont, the company became a standalone company in June 2019.','corteva.png',11),(38,'Dynatrace Inc.','DT','Dynatrace, Inc. is a global technology company listed on the NYSE that provides a software intelligence platform based on artificial intelligence (AI) and automation. Dynatrace technologies are used to monitor and optimize application performance, software development and security practices, IT infrastructure, and user experience for businesses and government agencies throughout the world. ','dynatrace.png',2),(39,'Planet Fitness','PLNT','Planet Fitness, Inc. is a fitness club franchise in the US with over 2,100 locations spread across all 50 states. It also has international locations in Canada, Mexico, Panama, and Australia, with 95% of its locations operated as independent franchises. First established in 1992 in Dover, New Hampshire, the company has its headquarters in Hampton, New Hampshire.','planetfit.png',9),(40,'Chart Industries','GTLS','Founded in 1992, Chart Industries Inc is a global manufacturer of engineered equipment designed for the industrial gas and energy industries. The company\'s products are used through the distribution, storage, production, and end-use stages of the liquid gas supply chain. With international operations, the company has its headquarters in Ball Ground, Georgia. ','chart.png',6),(41,'Privia Health','PRVA','Privia Health™ is a national physician platform transforming the healthcare delivery experience. We provide tailored solutions for physicians and providers, creating value and securing their future. ','privia.png',4),(42,'Vinci S.A','DG.PA','Vinci S.A. provides electrical grid and transport infrastructure, produces asphalt mixes, and builds and maintains roads, railways, and urban infrastructure. Created through a merger in 2000, the company has its headquarters in Rueil-Malmaison, France, and operates internationally. Vinci is listed on the Euronext Paris stock exchange under the ticker DG.PA. Learn about the latest DG.PA stock news by adding this instrument to your eToro watchlist.','vinci.png',5),(43,'Pinterest','PINS','Pinterest, Inc. is a leading social media provider operating internationally. The company offers a visual discovery engine for finding ideas, such as recipes and style inspiration. Founded in 2010, Pinterest has its headquarters in San Francisco, California.','pinterest.png',2),(44,'Cenovus Energy','CVE','Cenovus Energy is a Canadian company supplying energy services across Canada and the USA. Based in Calgary, the company was founded in 2009 and is engaged in developing, producing, and marketing various energy products including crude oil, natural gas liquids, and natural gas. The company has established natural gas and oil production in both Alberta and British Columbia and has part ownership over two refineries based in the USA.','cenovus.png',7),(45,'Vulcan Materials','VMC','Vulcan Materials Company engages in the production and supply of construction materials. Founded in 1909, the company was initially known as Virginia Holdco before it changed its name to Vulcan Materials Company after a merger with Vulcan Detinning Company in 1956 allowed it to gain access to capital markets. Headquartered in Birmingham, Alabama, the organisation operates primarily in the United States, with an international interest through its marine terminals and quarries located in British Columbia and the Yucatán Peninsula in Mexico.','vulcan.png',11),(46,'Globant SA','GLOB','Globant is an IT and Software Development company operating in Argentina, Colombia, Uruguay, the United Kingdom, Brazil, the United States, Canada, Peru, India, Mexico, Chile, Costa Rica, Ecuador, Spain, France, Germany, Romania and Belarus. It was formed in 2003 by Martín Migoya, Guibert Englebienne, Martín Umaran and Néstor Nocetti. It was founded in Buenos Aires, but currently is headquartered in Luxembourg and principally serves clients in the United States and United Kingdom. ','globant.png',2),(47,'Copa Holdings','CPA','Copa Holdings, SA is the parent company of Copa Airlines and its subsidiary, Copa Airlines Colombia. Based in Panama, the company was founded in 1947 and serves customers across North, Central, and South America, as well as within the Caribbean. Copa is a leading provider of both airline passenger and cargo services in the Latin American market, operating a fleet of 102 aircraft as of the end of 2019.','copa.png',9),(48,'TechnipFMC','FTI','TechnipFMC Plc offers a range of products, services, and fully integrated solutions to the traditional and new energies industries. Based in London, UK, the company was founded in 2015 and operates globally. TechnipFMC uses the ticker FTI on the NYSE. Chart FTI share price changes with the help of your eToro watchlist.','technip.png',5),(49,'Agnico Eagle','AEM','Agnico Eagle Mines explores, develops, and engages in the production of mineral properties. It is primarily involved in gold mining but also produces silver, zinc, and copper. Founded in 1953, the business operates internationally. It has headquarters in Toronto, Canada. Listed on the NYSE, its stock uses the AEM ticker. Follow AEM share price movements by making this instrument an entry on your eToro watchlist.','agnico.png',7),(50,'Waste Conn.','WCN','Waste Connections Inc is an integrated waste services company, engaged in the provision of waste collection, transport, disposal, and recycling services — including the treatment of non-hazardous oilfield waste, and services for the rail haul transport of cargo and solid waste containers. Founded in 1997 with headquarters in The Woodlands, Texas, the firm serves millions of residential and commercial customers across the United States and Canada. The Waste Connections Canadian headquarters are located in Vaughn, Ontario.','wastecon.png',11);
